\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b After the first class, she pulled out a grey neck scarf and wrapped it around her neck. She then searched through her locker while tucking her stubborn hair inside the scarf. I realized I had been looking at her for so long. There were very few in the class, most of the students had gone out for a short break. As she was about to close her locker she looked around as if she suspected I was staring and that is when our eyes interlocked which sent a cold chill down my spine and my heart fighting my small chest threatening to burst out if not given space to pass.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b My head started sending questions, \uc0{\u8220}Did she just catch me staring at her? What are you going to tell her? Just go out man, and pretend nothing happened\uc0{\u8221} as I kept looking at her with shy glances. Lost in her. }}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b She then got up from her seat. I broke my glances and pretended I wasn\uc0{\u8217}t looking at her. I brought out my book and acted like I was reading through it. A few minutes later I felt something walking right in front of me, she then sat next to me looking straight into my face. She looked at me as if she would ask why have you been staring at me? But to my surprise, she just smiled, a smile that looked more beautiful from a close range. She then took the novel from me \uc0{\u8220}You are reading it upside down, is that how you people read from your previous school?\uc0{\u8230} you must be a wizard if you can read the book upside down.\uc0{\u8221} as she left a smile.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 I didn\uc0{\u8217}t give her a response, my head had collided with my heart and the chaos needed an intervention from a mediator.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b \uc0{\u8220}Hi\uc0{\u8230},\uc0{\u8221} she said in her angelic voice which was made more sweeter by her smile.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b That voice lingered in my head for quite some seconds which left me dumbstruck, sending my lips trembling, formulating words in my mind but my mouth betrayed me. I replied to her \uc0{\u8220}I am\uc0{\u8230} hi, sorry. River And The Source\uc0{\u8221} }}\par
