\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b \uc0{\u8220}What I am saying is that you and this girl don\uc0{\u8217}t have a future at all. After here, when you are done with the last paper; you won\uc0{\u8217}t see each other again.\uc0{\u8221} He said laughing, \uc0{\u8220}Look at me. When the exams are finished, you will go home and she will go home. You will keep in touch for a few weeks then no communication after there. This is something I have experienced before, take it from the source.\uc0{\u8221} I reluctantly accepted it asking myself if this man has ever experienced such kind of love before or if he has ever seen a beautiful lady like Terry. \uc0{\u8220}I\uc0{\u8217}m sure there were no such ladies during his school period,\uc0{\u8221} I said to myself.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b I was let go after half an hour of lecture. Nothing was about to change anyway, because I kept everything on the line for her. Every second I was with her was just heavenly, a joy so sweet coming from the love chambers of my heart, and I was not ready to let go of such feelings for anything. I came out of the school compound having a lot of thought in my head. We had agreed before that I would walk her home and see where she lives, but my chances of doing that were slashed down by Mr. Director. To my surprise, she was waiting for me at a junction about 500 meters away from school. I couldn\uc0{\u8217}t believe it, wasn\uc0{\u8217}t this love? It was like I was in those movie scenes. }}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b I walked her home and while we were walking, she disclosed a lot of things like how she loves her stepsister who is 6 years old. It was the first time she was opening up to me. Her mother died when she was in class eight, and all the years they have been living with their stepmother. They don\uc0{\u8217}t get along with the stepmother but still, she loves her stepsister whom she takes care of during the holidays. She talked of how close they are with her sister and how much she adores her; she would style her hair during the weekends and spend the nights together, playing and laughing but she can\uc0{\u8217}t do that now. For the last 2 months the little girl was taken to her grandmother\uc0{\u8217}s house which was closer to the school, she is all lonely at home. I saw her wipe little tears hanging around her eyes begging to be let go. I was short of words but I found out the type she is. She has a soft spot for love despite all the treatment from her stepmother she still feels they are inseparable from her sister. She told me she wished she could go visit her just to see her smile kiss her tiny hands and sleep beside her. She craves her voice and everything about her little sister. Her eyes started getting red, I stopped her. \uc0{\u8220}Am jealous of her, why is she getting all the love.\uc0{\u8221} she chuckled while she adjusted her shirt collar and pushed away stubborn teardrops from the conjunction of her eyelids. }}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b \uc0{\u8220}Majun, I have never told anyone my story before only the school director knows it. Please keep this between us. You can come around anytime in the weekdays\uc0{\u8221} She smiled as if to say something. \uc0{\u8220}That is the building, we live on the ground floor house number three\uc0{\u8221} she pointed at the flat. I nodded and smiled back. \uc0{\u8220}This is it now, see you around next week buddy. I never had such a wonderful time before with any guy, I don\uc0{\u8217}t know why am saying this\uc0{\u8221} she said. But I knew why she was saying it, she liked me too but was afraid to say, so I assured her it was all good. \uc0{\u8220}Good moments are meant to be cherished and shared with people who are dear to us.\uc0{\u8221} She hugged me and walked away, I couldn\uc0{\u8217}t help but watch her go in and close the gate. My heart smiled as she walked in and since that day, I never recovered from the love portion or is it a spell? }}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b Time went by. Months passed and we were all short of nothing but a place to show our love since we were in school. They said love is a beautiful thing and yes, I agree with them. The time came for our final exams in high school. I was among the last group to finish the exams, she and others who took History and Government finished a day before. After my exams, I knew we now have time to give love all the time in the world to bloom into a beautiful rose. I went out on a hunt to get the love of my life whom I never told I loved in the den of her father and stepmother whom I don\uc0{\u8217}t know. After reaching the gate, my feet started to feel wobbly and my body was cold like a child suffering from malaria. Upon knocking at her door, a woman came out and gave me a look that made me stammered you might think it was Moses Osoro at that gate. \uc0{\u8220}Unataka aje? Na wewe ni nani?\uc0{\u8221} this is to say what do you want? And who are you? In Swahili. \uc0{\u8220}Mimi? Aah mimi ni nani?\uc0{\u8221} me? Who am I? I said in Swahili. I was sweating all over, my heart rate was so high she feared I might collapse at her doorstep. }}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b She closed the door and I started to walk away in shame. I heard someone opening the door again and I prayed that it was her. To my surprise it was her stepmother again, she called me back and handed me a glass of water and she started to talk \uc0{\u8220}Are you Majun?\uc0{\u8221} she asked \uc0{\u8220}Yes, I am Majun. Jones Majun\uc0{\u8221} I said as I sipped water. \uc0{\u8220}I saw your name on Terry\uc0{\u8217}s diary\uc0{\u8221} She paused and looked back inside again as if to confirm something, and she continued \uc0{\u8220}Let me take a guess, you are here to see Terry?\uc0{\u8221} she pulled her bra up, \uc0{\u8220}Yes, she had told me to come here and pick a bracelet,\uc0{\u8221} I said. \uc0{\u8220}Terry is not around she has been taken by her father to the village and I don\uc0{\u8217}t know when she will be back. So, don\uc0{\u8217}t ask me if I know when she will be back.\uc0{\u8221} It was at this time Mr. Kuria\uc0{\u8217}s words hit me \uc0{\u8220}After the last paper you will see her again\uc0{\u8221} I was heartbroken but not sad at all, I consoled myself even though I was disheartened. \uc0{\u8220}She was not mine. I didn\uc0{\u8217}t confess to her how I felt.\uc0{\u8221} Of the months we spent together I discovered a new feeling, a new entity within me, because she loved me. }}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b I walked away imagining her staring at me on the window as I walked away. I imagined her in every scenario as I retreated myself. It was one of the hardest things that struck my heart. As from that I never saw Terry again.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0\b I have never been a believer in love but this girl made me a worshipper, one thing I did realize is that with everything created in this world, love was created to neutralize everything. Even though life hurts so bad love will always be there to remind you of greater things. My love was wrecked when I lost Terry, so, when you find her, please tell her I still love her. \uc0{\u160}\uc0{\u160}}}\par
